class BtDeviceListConstantIterator

Detailed Description

BtDeviceListConstantReverseIterator is used to iterate a BtDeviceList in the reverse order. Dereferencing the iterator returns pointers or references to constant objects. So these objects can not be changed through this iterator.

BtDeviceListConstantReverseIterator BtDeviceListConstantReverseIterator::operator++ (  int   ) 
 

iterator increment operator (postfix)

operator++ is the postfix increment operator and is used to move the current position that the iterator is representing in a BtDeviceList forward to the next position in the list. Incrementing the position of a reverse iterator is the same as decrementing the position in a normal iterator.

Returns:
A BtDeviceListConstantReverseIterator that is representing the iterator before advancing. The iterator itself is either the next position in the BtDeviceList or the past-the-end iterator.

Reimplemented in BtDeviceListReverseIterator.

BtDeviceListConstantReverseIterator BtDeviceListConstantReverseIterator::operator-- (  int   ) 
 

iterator decrement operator (postfix)

operator-- is the postfix decrement operator and is used to move the current position that the iterator is representing in a BtDeviceList backward to the previous position in the list. Decrementing the position of a reverse iterator is the same as decrementing the position in a normal iterator.

Returns:
A BtDeviceListConstantReverseIterator that is representing the iterator before receding. The iterator itself is either the previous position in the BtDeviceList or the past-the-end iterator.
